text: Osiriaca is a monotypic moth genus of the family Crambidae described by Francis Walker in 1866. Its only species, Osiriaca ptousalis, described by the same author in 1859, is known from Australia. 200px ==References== Category:Spilomelinae Category:Moths of Australia Category:Monotypic moth genera Category:Crambidae genera Category:Taxa named by Francis Walker
